excerpt: 5,000-year span of fine & decorative arts ranging from a mummy to paintings by European masters.
detail_description: The Minneapolis Institute of Art, also known as Mia, is a renowned art museum boasting over 90,000 works from six continents spanning 5,000 years. Housed in a stunning Prairie Architecture building designed by legends like Louis Sullivan and Frank Lloyd Wright, Mia offers an open floor plan to showcase its diverse collections. Visitors can explore ancient artifacts like a mummy and European masterpieces alongside contemporary exhibits featuring artists such as Dawoud Bey and Kehinde Wiley.
name: Minneapolis Institute of Art

excerpt: Acclaimed venue featuring contemporary art in a variety of media, plus a sculpture garden & bistro.
detail_description: The Walker Art Center is a renowned venue showcasing contemporary art in various forms, along with a sculpture garden and bistro. While not always free, visitors can take advantage of events like Target Free Thursday Nights and First Free Saturdays for complimentary access to exhibitions, lectures, film screenings, and live performances. The center offers diverse experiences for art enthusiasts and families alike.
name: Walker Art Center

excerpt: History of the flour industry told through interactive exhibits in the rebuilt ruins of an old mill.
detail_description: Mill City Museum is a captivating destination that offers an immersive experience into the history of Minneapolis and the flour industry. Housed within the reconstructed ruins of the Washburn "A" Mill, visitors can explore interactive exhibits that narrate the city's evolution alongside the flour industry. The museum, located on the banks of the Mississippi Riverfront, provides insight into how this industry shaped Minneapolis' growth. As part of the St.
name: Mill City Museum

excerpt: Landmark venue for wide-ranging plays on 3 stages, full-service dining, several bars & river views.
detail_description: The Guthrie Theater, a renowned venue in Minneapolis, offers a diverse range of plays across its three stages. The theater also features full-service dining, multiple bars, and scenic river views. Established in 2006 to replace the original Guthrie Theater near the Walker Art Center, the new facility includes various amenities such as costume and set shops, storage spaces, classrooms, and a gift shop offering unique merchandise.
name: Guthrie Theater

excerpt: Biking & walking paths on this former railroad bridge with panoramic views of St. Anthony Falls.
detail_description: Stone Arch Bridge, located in downtown Minneapolis at the intersection of West River Road and Portland Ave, is a historic former railroad bridge that offers stunning panoramic views of St. Anthony Falls. Built in 1883 by James J. Hill, it served as a vital transportation link until 1965 and is now a symbol of the railroad age. This National Historic Engineering Landmark forms part of the two-mile St. Anthony Falls Heritage Trail, featuring pedestrian walkways and bicycle lanes for year-round outdoor enjoyment.
name: Stone Arch Bridge

excerpt: This modern stainless steel & brick building houses American & contemporary paintings plus ceramics.
detail_description: The Weisman Art Museum, designed by the renowned architect Frank O. Gehry, is a modern stainless steel and brick building located near the Mississippi River on the University of Minnesota campus. The museum's stunning exterior often draws attention from visitors due to its unique design, especially at sunset. Inside, it houses a diverse collection of over 25,000 works of art including American and contemporary paintings, ceramics, Korean furniture, and special exhibitions throughout the year.
name: Weisman Art Museum
address: 333 E River Rd, Minneapolis, MN 55455, USA

excerpt: An 11-acre preserve featuring a conservatory, an arbor & 40+ sculptures by notable modern artists.
detail_description: The Minneapolis Sculpture Garden is an 11-acre urban park adjacent to the Walker Art Center, showcasing over 40 captivating sculptures from renowned modern artists. One of its most iconic pieces is the giant spoon sculpture, Spoonbridge and Cherry by Claes Oldenburg. The garden offers free tours, outdoor concerts, and educational activities for all ages. Open year-round from dawn until midnight, it provides a unique blend of art and nature with its carefully curated landscape supporting wildlife and plants.
name: Minneapolis Sculpture Garden

excerpt: Cycling, walking & seasonal wading pools are big draws to these cascading falls in a namesake park.
detail_description: Minnehaha Falls is a stunning 53-foot waterfall located in Minnehaha Park, the most-visited park in Minneapolis. The falls are formed by the Minnehaha Creek, which flows from Lake Minnetonka to the Mississippi River.
name: Minnehaha Falls

excerpt: Home baseball stadium for the Minnesota Twins offering group & private behind-the-scenes tours.
detail_description: Target Field is the home stadium of the Minnesota Twins and offers both group and private behind-the-scenes tours. The stadium's sleek and modern design, featuring a large Minnie and Paul logo in center field, opened in 2010. Even if you're not there during baseball season, you can still visit the plaza and amphitheater without buying a ticket. Additionally, various restaurants have created attractive patio spaces from old warehouses around the stadium.
name: Target Field

excerpt: Stately museum & culture center featuring Swedish history exhibits, a mansion & art classes.
detail_description: The American Swedish Institute is a stately museum and culture center that showcases the rich history and heritage of the Scandinavian population in the United States. Established in 1929, it features informative talks, language-learning classes, and temporary exhibits. The institute comprises the modern Nelson Cultural Center and the historic Turnblad Mansion. Every holiday season, it hosts a traditional Scandinavian Christmas marketplace called Jul Shop, offering unique gifts and handcrafted items.
name: American Swedish Institute

excerpt: This grand church with stained-glass windows, shrines & an art gallery was America's first basilica.
detail_description: The Basilica of Saint Mary, located in downtown Minneapolis, is a historic Roman Catholic minor basilica and the first basilica established in America. This architectural masterpiece boasts stunning stained-glass windows, shrines, and an art gallery. Constructed in 1915, it is a prime example of Beaux Arts architecture and has been on the National Register of Historic Places since 1975.
name: Basilica of Saint Mary

excerpt: Housed in an old depot, this rock venue & tiny side bar have hosted & launched many acts since 1970.
detail_description: First Avenue is a legendary rock venue and bar located in an old depot that has been a pivotal space for launching musical acts since 1970. It gained fame as the concert hall featured in 'Purple Rain,' where Prince and The Revolution were the house band in the 1980s. Originally known as The Depot, it was ground zero for the local punk and hardcore scene, providing a platform for bands like the Replacements, Husker Du, and Soul Asylum.
name: First Avenue

excerpt: Bustling internationally themed market with stalls selling food & crafts from around the world.
detail_description: Midtown Global Market is a vibrant and diverse marketplace located in Minneapolis, offering an array of international foods, crafts, and cultural experiences. With over 50 vendors showcasing global produce, gourmet items, prepared foods, and unique gifts, visitors can explore the rich diversity of South Minneapolis. From Latin American arts at Arte Hispano to Scandinavian treats at Cafe Finspang, the market provides a sensory journey through different cultures.
name: Midtown Global Market
address: 920 E Lake St, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA

detail_description: U.S. Bank Stadium, located in Minneapolis, is a hub for sports and entertainment. It is home to the Minnesota Vikings NFL team and has hosted major events like Super Bowl LI. The stadium boasts a unique design with a translucent roof and pivoting glass doors, as well as the Legacy Ship featuring fan-donated bricks and historical markers. Visitors can take guided tours to learn about the stadium's history and architecture.
name: U.S. Bank Stadium

excerpt: Museum & education center for all ages offering exhibits on electricity, Ben Franklin & magnets.
detail_description: The Bakken Museum in Minneapolis is a captivating destination for visitors of all ages, offering an engaging exploration of science and innovation. The museum features exhibits on electricity, Ben Franklin, and magnets, showcasing 18th-century gadgets and gizmos introduced at Benjamin Franklin's house parties for scientists. Visitors can also experience a re-creation of Mary Shelley's legendary monster and engage in interactive activities like creating stop-motion movies and virtual art.
name: The Bakken Museum
address: 3537 Zenith Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55416, USA

excerpt: A 759-acre park offering year-round activities plus a lake, urban forest & chalet-style clubhouse.
detail_description: Theodore Wirth Regional Park, the largest city park in Minneapolis, covers 759 acres and offers a wide range of activities throughout the year. The park features a lake, urban forest, and chalet-style clubhouse. Visitors can enjoy playgrounds, walking trails, sports facilities, a wildflower garden and bird sanctuary, a quaking bog with boardwalk access, disc golf course, beach area, cross-country ski trails in winter and mountain biking in warmer months.
name: Theodore Wirth Regional Park
address: 1301 Theodore Wirth Pkwy, Golden Valley, MN 55422, USA

detail_description: Nicollet Mall, located in the heart of downtown Minneapolis, is a bustling street offering a variety of shopping, dining, and entertainment options. Visitors can enjoy strolling along this 12-block stretch that houses the famous Nicollet Skyway, providing sheltered access to numerous city blocks. The mall is also home to seasonal events like craft and farmers' markets as well as iconic landmarks such as the Mary Tyler Moore statue at the corner of 7th Street.
name: Nicollet Mall

excerpt: City park built around a historic old mill, featuring interpretive signs, walking & biking paths.
detail_description: Mill Ruins Park is a historic city park in Minneapolis, built around the remnants of old flour mills that were once part of the city's thriving industrial history. The park features interpretive signs, walking paths, and bridges that allow visitors to explore the preserved ruins of several mills. Set against the dramatic backdrop of St.
name: Mill Ruins Park
address: 102 Portland Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55401, USA

excerpt: Historic urban waterfall known for its hydroelectric dam & lock system & heritage trail loop.
detail_description: Saint Anthony Falls, located in Minneapolis, is a historic urban waterfall with a hydroelectric dam and lock system. In the 19th century, it was central to the Flour Milling Capital of the World, powering various mills. The Dakota people considered it a significant site for thousands of years. Overuse and poor engineering led to damage in the late 1800s, prompting improvements by the Army Corps of Engineers.
name: Saint Anthony Falls

detail_description: Mercado Central, located at the intersection of Lake St. and Bloomington Ave., is a vibrant marketplace housing over 30 Latino businesses offering a variety of goods and authentic Latin American cuisine. The exterior of the building is adorned with striking murals, adding to its charm. While it may not be as large as Midtown Global Market down the road, Mercado Central offers a diverse selection of food and locally made products.
name: Mercado Central
address: 1515 E Lake St, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA

excerpt: Riverside park featuring a playground, a boat dock & restrooms, plus walking/biking paths.
detail_description: Boom Island Park is a picturesque riverside park located in urban Minneapolis, offering a range of activities for visitors. The park features a playground, boat dock, restrooms, walking and biking paths, as well as picnic areas and a boat launch. Situated on a former river island with historical significance as a logging sorting station, the park now provides scenic views of the Mississippi River and the Minneapolis skyline.
name: Boom Island Park
address: 724 Sibley St NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

excerpt: Civil Warera military structure & museum with a drum corp, historical re-enactments & a gift shop.
detail_description: Historic Fort Snelling is a significant National Historic Landmark that dates back to 1819. It played a crucial role in the founding of St. Paul and was strategically located at the confluence of the Mississippi River and the Minnesota River. The fort features well-preserved bulwarks and palisades, offering insights into Minnesota's military history from pre-Civil War to World Wars I and II, as well as its involvement in fur and slave trade.
name: Historic Fort Snelling
address: 200 Tower Ave, St Paul, MN 55111, USA

excerpt: This lake is surrounded by parks & features beaches, trails, boating, a bandshell & skyline views.
detail_description: Lake Harriet, located in Minneapolis, is a picturesque spot surrounded by parks and offering various recreational activities. Visitors can enjoy beaches, trails, boating, and skyline views. The area is popular during late spring and summer, attracting families and individuals who come to relax by the lake. The lake's charm extends to its nearby cafes where patrons can savor delightful meals amidst a warm ambiance.
name: Lake Harriet

excerpt: Museum featuring galleries of Russian art & artifacts, plus events, classes & a gift shop.
detail_description: The Museum of Russian Art (TMORA) is a cultural gem featuring galleries filled with Russian art and artifacts. Visitors can also enjoy events, classes, and a unique gift shop offering artisan goods reminiscent of Eastern European markets. The shop showcases hand-painted Matryoshka dolls, exquisite amber jewelry, religious icons, Russian chocolate, canned goods, and cooking staples. TMORA provides an opportunity to explore the culture shaped by a communist state through its exhibitions and explanations from their perspective.
name: The Museum of Russian Art

excerpt: Saturday marketplace open for local produce, art, live music & kids activities.
detail_description: Mill City Farmers Market is a vibrant marketplace in Minneapolis, offering a wide array of locally sourced products including produce, flowers, ceramics, and jewelry. Visitors can enjoy live music, cooking demonstrations, and activities for kids while shopping. The market is committed to fostering a sense of community by supporting over 100 local farmers and food producers. Founded by renowned restaurateur Brenda Langton in 2006, the market specializes in zero-waste practices and offers organic produce, meat, and dairy products.
name: Mill City Farmers Market

detail_description: Located in downtown Minneapolis, Target Center is a versatile arena that underwent a $140 million renovation in 2017. It is home to the NBA's Minnesota Timberwolves and the WNBA's Minnesota Lynx, both of which have achieved significant success. The venue hosts over 1,000,000 guests annually and attracts renowned touring artists, family shows, and major sporting events.
name: Target Center

detail_description: The Minneapolis Central Library, established in 1885 as the city's first public library, is situated in downtown Minneapolis. It features an extensive children's section and a renowned comic book collection. The Pohlad Hall Theater hosts monthly educational programs for children, offering animated shorts, live entertainment, free books, readings, and refreshments.
name: Minneapolis Central Library

excerpt: Opened in 1921, this restored, 2,579-seat theater offers Broadway musicals, concerts & other events.
detail_description: The Orpheum Theatre, located on Hennepin Avenue, has a rich history dating back to 1921 when it was the largest vaudeville house in the country. The theater, with its distinctive luminous sign and seating for 2,579 people, has hosted performances by renowned artists such as Prince, Neil Young, and The Cure. It also serves as a prime stage for touring Broadway musicals like Mean Girls and Rent.
name: Orpheum Theatre

detail_description: The Grand Rounds Scenic Byway is a sprawling network of urban parks in the United States, offering visitors an extensive and picturesque outdoor experience. This renowned byway has been recognized for its historical significance and has been nominated for inclusion on the National Register of Historic Places. With its free entrance, it provides a great opportunity to explore nature within city limits.
name: Grand Rounds Scenic Bywy

detail_description: The Minnesota State Fair, also known as "The Great Minnesota Get-Together," is a highly anticipated event in the Midwest that attracts over 1.7 million visitors during its 12-day run in late August and early September. The fair offers a wide array of unique and indulgent foods, from mac and cheese cupcakes to maple bacon funnel cakes, making it a must-visit for food enthusiasts.
name: Minnesota State Fair Compeer Arena
address: 1871 Judson Ave, St Paul, MN 55108, USA

excerpt: The Mississippi River bisects this urban research university known for management, education & law.
detail_description: The University of Minnesota is a renowned urban research institution located between Mississippi and University Avenues in Minneapolis. It offers four coordinate campuses across the state. The university boasts top-notch amenities and a prime location high above the 35W Bridge, providing stunning views of the Mississippi River and Downtown Minneapolis skyline. The Campus Club at the university is an ideal venue for weddings, offering a blend of historic charm and modern elegance.
name: University of Minnesota

excerpt: Lake for canoeing, swimming & windsurfing, with adjacent parks & trails for biking, skating & more.
detail_description: Bde Maka Ska, formerly known as Lake Calhoun, is a stunning 401-acre lake nestled in Minneapolis that offers a plethora of outdoor activities. This beautiful spot is perfect for canoeing, swimming, and windsurfing, with ample parks and trails nearby for biking and skating. Renamed in 2018 to honor its Dakota heritage, Bde Maka Ska translates to 'White Earth Lake,' reflecting its rich cultural history.
name: Bde Maka Ska

excerpt: Scenic setting providing biking & walking trails, water activities & a castle-inspired band shell.
detail_description: Lake Harriet Bandshell Park is a picturesque setting nestled in the heart of Minneapolis, offering biking and walking trails, water activities, and a castle-inspired band shell. The bandshell has been hosting concerts since 1883 and is a popular spot for professional portraits due to its large soft box-like structure. The park's natural beauty makes it a sought-after location for engagement and family photos, with charming lakeside paths, docks, blooming gardens, and stunning sunset lighting.
name: Lake Harriet Bandshell Park
address: 4135 W Lake Harriet Pkwy, Minneapolis, MN 55409, USA

excerpt: Compact, upstairs lounge offering craft cocktails & American plates in a dimly lit, urbane setting.
detail_description: Parlour is a cozy, upstairs lounge known for its craft cocktails and American plates in a sophisticated setting. Located beneath Borough, it's the perfect spot for post-dinner drinks. The menu features fantastic cocktails like the Sunny Place for Shady People and classic favorites such as the Parlour Old Fashioned and seasonal Manhattan. Additionally, Parlour offers curbside pickup and delivery through Bitesquad for their Minneapolis and St.
name: Parlour
address: 730 N Washington Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55401, USA

detail_description: Bauhaus Brew Labs is a must-visit spot in the Northeast, Minneapolis. Located in the arts district, this brewery offers a unique experience with its large patio overlooking train tracks. The addition of Animales Barbeque Co. has enhanced the experience, offering refreshing drinks like Short Pants shandy and pineapple lemonade to complement their flavorful ribs.
name: Bauhaus Brew Labs
address: 1315 Tyler St NE, Minneapolis, MN 55413, USA

excerpt: Charming, mainly residential Loring Park is known for its large namesake green space, which has a lake and extensive walking and cycling paths. Upscale New American restaurants, cozy cafes and independent shops that range from bicycle stores to bridal boutiques, dot the surrounding streets. The area is also home to the early-1900s Basilica of St. Mary and the Minneapolis Convention Center.
detail_description: Loring Park is a delightful neighborhood with a predominantly residential feel. The area is famous for its expansive green space, which includes a beautiful lake and extensive paths perfect for leisurely walks and bike rides. The neighborhood streets are lined with upscale New American restaurants, charming cafes, and an array of independent shops offering everything from bicycles to bridal attire. Additionally, Loring Park is home to the historic Basilica of St. Mary dating back to the early 1900s and the bustling Minneapolis Convention Center.
name: Loring Park

detail_description: Minneapolis City Hall, located at 315 4th Street South in downtown Minneapolis, is a grand castle-like building constructed in the Richardsonian Romanesque style from 1885 to 1905. Standing over 100 feet tall with a clock tower reaching 365 feet high, it presents a striking contrast to the modern buildings surrounding it. The City Beautiful Plan, developed by architect Edward H.
name: Minneapolis City Hall

excerpt: Tours of a distinctive tower skyscraper with 360-degree views from the 31st floor (up to 30 miles).
detail_description: The Foshay Museum and Observation Deck, located within the iconic Foshay Tower in downtown Minneapolis, offers visitors a unique experience. The museum delves into the history of the 32-story skyscraper, originally built in 1929 as a tribute to the Washington Monument by Wilbur Foshay. It showcases the story of its construction and its eccentric creator.
name: Foshay Museum and Observation Deck
address: 821 S Marquette Ave 30th floor, Minneapolis, MN 55402, USA

excerpt: Circa-1954 beer and burger joint celebrated for its cheese-stuffed patty, the Jucy Lucy.
detail_description: Matt's Bar and Grill is a classic beer and burger joint that has been around since 1954. It is famous for its iconic cheese-stuffed patty, the Jucy Lucy. Stepping into Matt's Bar feels like taking a trip back in time, with its unchanged decor and ambiance. The bar holds historical significance as one of the feuding establishments claiming to have originated the Jucy Lucy, along with the 5-8 Club.
name: Matt's Bar and Grill

excerpt: Also known as the Warehouse District, the North Loop is a vibrant neighborhood known for its cool start-up vibe, innovative restaurants, hip bars and gay nightspots. Converted warehouses from the late 19th and early 20th centuries contain indie fashion and design shops, and the Minneapolis Farmers Market sells produce, locally made snacks and candy. Minnesota Twins baseball fans head to Target Field on game days.
detail_description: The North Loop, also referred to as the Warehouse District, is a lively neighborhood with a trendy startup atmosphere. It's famous for its innovative dining scene, stylish bars, and vibrant gay nightlife. The area features converted warehouses housing indie fashion and design stores, while the Minneapolis Farmers Market offers locally produced snacks and fresh produce. Additionally, sports enthusiasts can catch Minnesota Twins baseball games at Target Field on game days.
name: North Loop

excerpt: Arepas (cornmeal cakes filled with meat & cheese) are the specialty of this festive Latin eatery.
detail_description: Hola Arepa is a vibrant Latin eatery that specializes in arepas, which are cornmeal cakes filled with a variety of delicious ingredients such as meat and cheese. The restaurant offers a festive atmosphere with boozy slushies and lush greenery, creating the feeling of brunching in a lively rainforest treehouse.
name: Hola Arepa

detail_description: Paradise Charter Cruises & Minneapolis Queen offers public and private cocktail, dinner, and sightseeing cruises along the Mississippi River. The 90-minute trips provide panoramic views of downtown Minneapolis, suburban foliage, and architecture. The Minneapolis Queen is a must-visit for a traditional river cruise experience with happy hour pizza, sightseeing, and guided tours. While evening wine cruises cater to adults, day tours are recommended for families with kids.
name: Paradise Charter Cruises & Minneapolis Queen
address: 2150 W River Pkwy, Minneapolis, MN 55454, USA

detail_description: Nestled in north Minneapolis, the Minnesota African American Heritage Museum & Gallery is a vibrant nonprofit establishment dedicated to celebrating and preserving the rich history and culture of African Americans in Minnesota. Open from Tuesday to Saturday, this museum offers free admission and showcases an array of both permanent and rotating exhibits that highlight significant contributions from early African-American settlers during the Great Migration.
name: Minnesota African American Heritage Museum & Gallery
address: 1256 N Penn Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55411, USA

excerpt: This lifeguard-supervised beach offers opportunities for swimming, fishing & boating.
detail_description: Cedar Lake East Beach, also known as Hidden Beach, is a serene and secluded spot in Minneapolis. Tucked away between lush greenery, this small sandy beach offers swimming, fishing, and boating opportunities under the supervision of lifeguards. It used to be a nudist beach and was popular among counter-culturists. The beach is dog- and kid-friendly and features a mud bath slightly to the east.
name: Cedar Lake East Beach
address: 2000 S Upton Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55405, USA

detail_description: When visiting Minneapolis, you'll likely explore the Minneapolis Skyway System, a 9.5-mile network of elevated walkways spanning 80 city blocks in downtown. While locals use it for daily commutes, tourists find it an intriguing attraction. This interconnected pathway is especially convenient during cold weather, offering a unique way to navigate the city while staying warm and sheltered from the elements.
name: Minneapolis Skyway System

detail_description: When in Minneapolis, a visit to US Bank Stadium is a must. As the home of the Minnesota Vikings and the host of the 2018 Superbowl, it's an iconic venue that showcases Minnesota pride. The stadium also made history by hosting the world's first 'zero waste' Superbowl. In addition to professional sports events, it hosts high school football league games, offering visitors a chance to experience local sports culture.
name: us bank stadium

detail_description: Located in the bustling downtown area of Minneapolis, The Commons is a spacious urban park that covers two blocks and 4.2 acres. It is thoughtfully designed to create an expansive outdoor space surrounded by buildings, with the city's skyline providing a picturesque backdrop on one side and the impressive U.S. Bank Stadium dominating the view on the other.
name: The Commons

detail_description: Located on Nicollet Mall, the Mary Tyler Moore Statue is a beloved attraction in Minneapolis. The statue commemorates the iconic moment from the opening credits of 'The Mary Tyler Moore Show' where Mary throws her tam in the air. This landmark celebrates the character of Mary Richards, known for her independence and humor, and has become a popular tourist destination.
name: 700 Nicollet Mall

excerpt: Celebrated urban lake featuring an ice-skating rink, fishing pier, paved jogging paths & dog park.
detail_description: Lake of the Isles is a popular urban lake that offers various activities for visitors. It features an ice-skating rink, fishing pier, paved jogging paths, and a dog park. The dog park provides ample space for canines to run and play in a safely enclosed area, with a designated section for smaller dogs.
name: Lake of the Isles

excerpt: Classic 1940s movie theater with high-back seats & a mod lobby lounge, showing a range of films.
detail_description: Riverview Theater is a classic 1940s movie theater located in the Howe neighborhood of Minneapolis. It offers a nostalgic movie experience with its 1950s style, featuring high-back rocker seats and digital sound. The theater showcases a variety of films, from Hollywood blockbusters to niche art films, in its 700-seater auditorium. With affordable ticket prices for children and special deals on matinees and Tuesdays, it's a great place for family outings.
name: Riverview Theater
